PROJECT 1 – Attendance Tracker Automation
Scenario
HR maintains employee attendance manually.
You want to:

Count total Present days

Mark status: Good / Low Attendance

Highlight low attendance (<20 days)

 Sample Data
EmpID	Name	PresentDays
101	Ravi	22
102	Ananya	18
103	Kiran	25
104	Priya	15

 Solution
Sub AttendanceReport()

    Dim lastRow As Long
    Dim i As Long
    
    lastRow = Cells(Rows.Count, 1).End(xlUp).Row
    
    Range("D1").Value = "Status"
    
    For i = 2 To lastRow
        
        If Cells(i, 3).Value < 20 Then
            Cells(i, 4).Value = "Low"
            Cells(i, 3).Interior.Color = RGB(255, 0, 0)
        Else
            Cells(i, 4).Value = "Good"
        End If
        
    Next i
    
    MsgBox "Attendance Report Ready!"

End Sub

 PROJECT 2 – Salary Increment Automation
 Scenario
Company gives:
10% increment if salary < 30000
5% increment if salary ≥ 30000

Sample Data
EmpID	Name	Salary
201	Ravi	25000
202	Priya	35000
203	Kiran	28000

 Solution
Sub SalaryIncrement()

    Dim lastRow As Long
    Dim i As Long
    
    lastRow = Cells(Rows.Count, 1).End(xlUp).Row
    
    Range("D1").Value = "New Salary"
    
    For i = 2 To lastRow
        
        If Cells(i, 3).Value < 30000 Then
            Cells(i, 4).Value = Cells(i, 3).Value * 1.1
        Else
            Cells(i, 4).Value = Cells(i, 3).Value * 1.05
        End If
        
    Next i

End Sub

 PROJECT 3 – Sales Cleaning & Summary Tool
 Scenario
Sales file contains duplicates.
You want:
Remove duplicates
Sort by Sales (High to Low)
Calculate total & average sales

 Sample Data
OrderID	Region	Sales
1001	South	5000
1002	North	7000
1001	South	5000
1003	West	4000

Solution
Sub SalesCleaner()

    Dim lastRow As Long
    lastRow = Cells(Rows.Count, 1).End(xlUp).Row
    
    Range("A1:C" & lastRow).RemoveDuplicates Columns:=1, Header:=xlYes
    
    Range("A1:C" & lastRow).Sort Key1:=Range("C2"), Order1:=xlDescending, Header:=xlYes
    
    Range("E1").Value = "Total Sales"
    Range("E2").Value = Application.WorksheetFunction.Sum(Range("C2:C" & lastRow))
    
    Range("E3").Value = "Average Sales"
    Range("E4").Value = Application.WorksheetFunction.Average(Range("C2:C" & lastRow))
    
End Sub


 PROJECT 4 – Monthly Sales Report Generator
 Scenario
Manager wants:
Clean report sheet
Copy data
Show total sales
Create pivot by region

 Sample Data (Sheet: RawData)
OrderID	Region	Sales
1001	South	5000
1002	North	7000
1003	West	4000
1004	South	6000

 Solution
Sub GenerateSalesReport()

    Dim wsRaw As Worksheet
    Dim wsReport As Worksheet
    Dim lastRow As Long
    
    Set wsRaw = Sheets("RawData")
    
    On Error Resume Next
    Sheets("Report").Delete
    On Error GoTo 0
    
    Sheets.Add After:=Sheets(Sheets.Count)
    ActiveSheet.Name = "Report"
    
    Set wsReport = Sheets("Report")
    
    lastRow = wsRaw.Cells(wsRaw.Rows.Count, 1).End(xlUp).Row
    
    wsRaw.Range("A1:C" & lastRow).Copy wsReport.Range("A1")
    
    wsReport.Range("E1").Value = "Total Sales"
    wsReport.Range("E2").Value = Application.WorksheetFunction.Sum(wsReport.Range("C2:C" & lastRow))
    
    MsgBox "Report Generated!"

End Sub

 PROJECT 5 – One-Click Dashboard Refresh
 Scenario

Company dashboard has multiple pivot tables.
Need one-click refresh.

 Solution
Sub RefreshAllPivotTables()

    Dim ws As Worksheet
    Dim pt As PivotTable
    
    For Each ws In ThisWorkbook.Worksheets
        For Each pt In ws.PivotTables
            pt.RefreshTable
        Next pt
    Next ws
    
    MsgBox "Dashboard Updated!"

End Sub


